rComments: It WAS a 400-level class and is expected to be challenging, but he could have made it much easier just when it came to knowing what we were supposed to be learning. The lectures really weren't helpful with the homework and tests. He is obviously a really smart guy, but it's just frustrating when he can't explain things to us non-geniuses.

It's near impossible to fail this course if you complete the homework assignments on time.  Tests were a tad more difficult than the practice tests led me to believe.  Still, if you've got a good grasp of basic algebra, you're more than qualified for this gen-ed.  He's more than willing to help students who have questions, however.
Pretty easy teacher, but material on tests are covered too much. You have to read the book to understand anything.

Tony Wong is a funny guy and all, but his tests are ridiculous! They are never anything like the practice exams! Also they grade homework way too hard. Online quizzes are an easy A. You will need the book. Take this class if you like math/physics, but otherwise don't, it's a tricky GenEd.
